nciThesaurus.definition: A recombinant therapeutic agent which is chemically identical to or similar to the endogenous cytokine interleukin-18 (IL-18). Produced primarily by macrophages, IL-18 induces the production of interferon-gamma (IFN-gamma), and enhances the activity of natural killer (NK) and cytotoxic T lymphocytes (CTL).  As a potential immunotherapeutic agent, iboctadekin displays antitumor effects in vitro and in animal models.
synonyms: Human Interleukin-18 (Recombinant, Expressed in Escherichia coli)
